I've had good and bad service, but this really took the cake. First, there was an issue with mobile orders (I was ordering in person). I get that technology is not always reliable, so I waited patiently. However, over the course of 8/10 minutes, no one from behind the bar acknowledged myself or anyone in line. The gentleman at the register kept asking for help, while the two behind the bar kept rolling their eyes and not helping him at all  Finally, Tania came up to the bar to help. I ordered my two items and said I had a reward for one. She said, "What reward do you have, cause you don't have one." I showed her my birthday reward, to which I was then scolded for not telling her birthday reward and that it would have been my fault I was charged for two items. I use scolded because it was not funny/silly, but it was a sarcastic, "This is all your fault" manner. I walked away and waited with everyone else patiently - which is less then I can say for most people. Finally, everyone (those before and after me) had their items and I was left with my items forgotten. Tania then brought my food half way to me and got distracted so I had to wait longer for her to give me my food.  All in all, it was about a 25 minute experience that set a terrible tone for the beginning of my birthday.
